replies.body:
As a jungler I can tell you that this isn't the case. Many people see junglers as taking over the game because they don't think about all the time good junglers lose games. If you play jungle you will realize how reliant on your laners you actually are.  The real issue in your scenario is that you and your bot lane are not securing river vision. When mid and bot are ahead and they secure bottomside river there is nothing a jungler can do. He can't gank mid or bot without exposing himself in the river and it is usually too risky for him to go for drag. On the other hand, your team has control of drag and can easily move from one lane to another. Also, if mid and bot towers are down, the enemy jungler will usually have to forfeit up his entire botside jungle. The only thing a jungler can do from that point is to play around his top side/top laner, and top is arguably the lane that has the least effect on the game (this patch). Also mid and bot scale harder than junglers most of the time so even if you can't shut down their jungler, if you don't lose your lead he will become irrelevant. 

                       Ultimately though you see it as being the jungler, it's usually the game state that is out of control. Instead of blaming the jungler use your advantage to gain vision control then the enemy jungler will have no opportunity to gank you, and if you can't control vision, because your jungle and botlane are useless, then there is nothing you can do, league is a team game and the enemy jungle had the better team, it's unfortunate but unavoidable. 

P.S. the only reason people think junglers have control of the game is because the junglers don't have waves or towers to protect. So when a jungle gets fed he can move around freely and influence all the lanes. but in reality, a fed mid top supp or adc can do the same thing after they take tower, with the added bonus of having more gold and xp from lane farm. That's why when an enemy botlane gets fed it is so oppressive because you know have two laners that can roam. If your having trouble winning games, eventhough you are stomping your lane, you should learn better macro and stop blaming the jungler {{sticker:sg-miss-fortune}}
